modules.description: This module provides low-level operations for reading binary data (bytes, integers, marshaled values) and high-level line-based processing, including Windows EOL handling, along with file positioning and metadata access. It operates on input channels (`In_channel.t`) connected to sources like files and sockets, supporting use cases such as efficient file parsing, cross-platform text processing, and managing channel lifetimes to mitigate garbage collection overhead from frequent allocations.

This module provides operations for creating, writing to, and managing output channels, enabling blocking writes to destinations like files and sockets with support for strings, binary data, and structured formats such as S-expressions. It includes utilities for channel lifecycle management (close, flush), formatted printing, and direct output to standard streams, suitable for applications requiring precise I/O control, though creating many channels may affect garbage collection due to finalizer overhead.

This module provides direct access to standard input/output channels and operations for reading from and writing to them. It supports concrete tasks like line-based text processing, binary data manipulation, and formatted output to standard streams. Key data types include `In_channel.t` and `Out_channel.t`, used for handling input and output sources such as files and sockets.
